   ERROR: 2026-03-18 06:16:30,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  217: C:\Users\WIN10 HOME 22H2\Downloads\email project\PROJECT_REPORT.md:25: #13-conclusion: No such file or directory
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:30,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. What is This Project?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:30,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:30,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Email OAuth Client
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:30,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is a web-based email client application built using Python and the Flask web framework.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It allows users to securely log in with their Google account and view the latest 10 emails from their Gmail inbox — all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: without ever sharing their Google password with the application.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application uses 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OAuth 2.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Open Authorization), which is the industry-standard protocol used by Google,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Facebook, GitHub, and virtually every major technology company to allow third-party applications to access user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data safely.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In simple terms, think of it like this: instead of giving your house key to a stranger, you open the door yourself and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: allow them to look inside — but they cannot touch or take anything. That is exactly what this application does with your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gmail inbox.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. What Does This Project Do?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application performs the following core functions:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Feature | Description |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Google Sign-In
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Users click a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Login with Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  button and are redirected to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s official login page. The application never sees or stores the user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s password. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fetch 10 Latest Emails
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After login, the application uses the Gmail API to retrieve the 10 most recent emails from the user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s inbox. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Display Email Details
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | For each email, the application displays the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sender
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Subject Line
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Date
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , and a short 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Preview Snippet
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  of the email body. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Smart Categorization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Each email is automatically assigned a category
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Important, Work/Jobs, Social, Notifications, Promotions, or Other) based on the sender and subject line. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Search 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Filter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | A search bar allows users to filter their emails using keywords or Gmail search operators (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from:linkedin
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: subject:invoice
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ). |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Secure Logout
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Users can log out at any time, which completely
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clears their session data from the server. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. What Problem Does It Solve?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When developers or students need to build an application that reads emails, they face a significant challenge: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: how
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: do you access a user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s email without asking for their password?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Traditionally, email clients required users to enter their username and password directly into the application. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: approach has several serious problems:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Security Risk:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If the application is compromised, the attacker now has the user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s password.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trust Issue:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Users are understandably reluctant to type their password into an unknown application.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No Granular Control:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Once you give your password, the application can do anything — read, send,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: delete emails — with no restrictions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Solution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This project solves all three problems by implementing 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OAuth 2.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No password is ever shared.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The user logs in directly on Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s own website.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trust is established through Google.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Users see Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s familiar login page, not a random form.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Granular permissions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The application only requests 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gmail.readonly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  access — it can read emails
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cannot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  send, modify, or delete anything.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. How Does This Project Work?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Here is a step-by-step walkthrough of exactly what happens when a user uses the application:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 1: User Visits the Application
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The user opens 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: https://email-oauth-client.onrender.com
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in their browser. They see a clean,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dark-themed login page with a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Login with Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  button.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 2: User Clicks 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Login with Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application generates a special URL that points to Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s OAuth consent screen. This URL contains:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client ID
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (a unique identifier registered with Google).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scope
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gmail.readonly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) — telling Google exactly what permission is being requested.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: redirect URI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — the URL where Google should send the user back after login.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: state token
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — a random string to prevent forgery attacks (CSRF protection).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 3: User Logs In on Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Website
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The user is now on Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s official website (accounts.google.com). They enter their Google email and password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: directly on Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s page. The application never sees this information.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 4: User Grants Permission
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Google shows the user a consent screen explaining that 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Email OAuth Client wants to view your Gmail messages.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The user clicks 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Allow.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 5: Google Sends Back an Authorization Code
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Google redirects the user back to the application
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s callback URL (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: /oauth2callback
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) with a temporary 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: authorization code
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in the URL.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 6: Application Exchanges the Code for an Access Token
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s backend (Python server) takes this authorization code and sends it directly to Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s token server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: along with the application
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client Secret
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (a private password only the server knows). Google verifies everything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and responds with an 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Access Token
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 7: Application Fetches Emails Using the Access Token
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application uses this Access Token to make an authorized request to the Gmail API. It asks for the 10 most
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recent emails in the user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s inbox. The Gmail API returns the email data.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 8: Emails Are Displayed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application processes the raw email data, categorizes each email, and renders a beautiful inbox page showing all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 10 emails with their sender, subject, date, preview, and category badge.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5. The Logic Behind the Project
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: File-by-File Breakdown
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The project is organized into clearly separated modules, each handling one specific responsibility:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Configuration Manager
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This file loads all sensitive information (Client ID, Client Secret, Flask Secret Key) from 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: environment variables
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: never hardcodes secrets. It also defines the Gmail API scope (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gmail.readonly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) and the OAuth redirect URI.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: auth.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — OAuth Authentication Engine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This file contains the core OAuth logic:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:31,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: get_auth_flow()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Creates a Google OAuth Flow object configured with the application
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credentials.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: get_authorization_url()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Generates the Google consent screen URL with the correct
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: parameters.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exchange_code_for_credentials()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Takes the temporary authorization code from Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and exchanges it for a permanent Access Token.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credentials_to_session()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  / 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credentials_from_session()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Converts OAuth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credentials to/from a format that can be stored in Flask
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s encrypted session cookie.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gmail_service.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Gmail API Communication
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This file handles all communication with Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Gmail API:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: get_gmail_service()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Builds an authorized Gmail API service object using the user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Access
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,146:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fetch_latest_emails()
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Uses 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HTTP Batch Requests
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (a performance optimization) to fetch
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all 10 emails in a single network round-trip instead of making 10 separate requests. Each email is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: then passed through the categorizer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: utils/email_classifier.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Smart Email Categorizer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This file contains a keyword-based classification engine that assigns each email to one of six categories:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Category | Detection Logic |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Important
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Subject or sender contains: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: security
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: alert
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: verification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Work / Jobs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Subject contains job-related keywords, or sender is Indeed, LinkedIn, Glassdoor |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Social
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Sender domain is linkedin.com, twitter.com, facebook.com, or instagram.com |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Notifications
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Subject
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: contains: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: notification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: update
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: activity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Promotions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Subject contains: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: offer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discount
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: deal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: promotion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Default category if no keywords match |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: app.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Flask Web Server (The Central Hub)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is the main application file that ties everything together. It defines five routes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Route | Purpose |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GET /
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Renders the login page |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GET /login
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Redirects the user to Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s OAuth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consent screen |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GET /oauth2callback
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Handles Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s redirect after user grants permission |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GET
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: /emails
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Fetches and displays the user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 10 latest emails |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GET /logout
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Clears the session and redirects to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the home page |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6. The Role of OAuth 2.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is OAuth 2.0?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OAuth 2.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Open Authorization 2.0) is an industry-standard authorization framework. It allows a third-party
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: application to obtain limited access to a user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s account on another service (like Google, Facebook, or GitHub) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: without the user ever revealing their password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to the third-party application.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How OAuth 2.0 Works in This Project
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There are 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: four participants
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in the OAuth flow:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Participant | Role in This Project |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Resource Owner
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | The user (you) who owns the Gmail account |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | The Email OAuth Client application (our Flask app) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authorization Server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s OAuth server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (accounts.google.com) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Resource Server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Gmail API (googleapis.com) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The OAuth 2.0 Flow (Authorization Code Grant)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This project uses the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authorization Code Grant
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  flow, which is the most secure OAuth flow for web applications:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client → Authorization Server:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I am app X, and I want to read this user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Gmail.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authorization Server → User:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: App X wants to read your Gmail. Do you allow this?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: User → Authorization Server:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Yes, I allow it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authorization Server → Client:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Here is a temporary authorization code.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client → Authorization Server:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Here is the code + my secret password. Give me an Access Token.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authorization Server → Client:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Verified. Here is your Access Token.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  7 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client → Resource Server:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Here is my Access Token. Give me the user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s emails.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  8 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Resource Server → Client:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token is valid. Here are the 10 latest emails.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why OAuth 2.0 is Important
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Without OAuth | With OAuth |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | User gives password to the app | User logs in only on Google
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s page |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:32,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | App
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: has full account access | App only gets 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gmail.readonly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  permission |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | If app is hacked, password is exposed | If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: app is hacked, only a temporary token is exposed |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | User cannot revoke access easily | User can revoke access
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anytime from Google Settings |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Scope: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gmail.readonly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application only requests the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gmail.readonly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  scope. This means:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ✅ Can read email messages
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ✅ Can list emails in the inbox
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ❌ Cannot send emails
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ❌ Cannot delete emails
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ❌ Cannot modify labels or settings
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-18 06:16:33,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ❌ Cannot access Google Drive, Calendar, or any other Google service
